primary roles & responsibilities:
seek opportunities for business development within a defined area or sector;
plan persuasive approaches and pitches that will convince potential clients to do business with the company;
develop proposals that speak to the client’s needs, concerns, and objectives;
create, negotiate, and close commercial agreements.
education:
possess a bachelor’s degree or higher in business administration, sales management, marketing, or a related field with a strong academic record.
work experience:
have at least 2 years of experience in a corporate or business-focused environment.
demonstrate a proven track record of successfully securing new business through effective pitches.

responsibilities:
commercial
to head the commercial team in all aspects of commercial-related project management from pre-, during, and post-tender stages for the business project;
to lead and project-managed the commercial aspect of equipment sales process in consideration of all internal and external compliance issues as well as risk factors management such as using the internal control system (iks) or 4-eye-principle method, etc;
to support multi-national projects from inception to finalization for the commercial aspects in project management;
to be overall responsible of contract terms & conditions, contract analysis and active claim management for prevention & generation for the business project;
to ensure overall compliance of the business project.
accounting
to oversee account receivables management, supervise full set’s of account and audit management.
to coordinate and resolve all commercial related issues with all relevant departments from engineering, workshop assembly to field services etc in all overarching areas;
to be an active business partner in the business fields and various operational areas;
knowledge of trade securities is necessary.
financial and management
to work with overseas senior management team in setting financial targets and budget development goals as well as to monitor it throughout the financial year;
to be overall responsible for treasury management which involves liquidity management, cash management banking relationships etc., within the subsidiary;
forecast planning for project-related businesses and cost center planning at the business-unit level;
to analysis project reports so as to provide suggestions for future improvement and propose key drivers in business planning and decisions-making activities;
to monitor the performance of commercial activities using key metrics and preparing reports for the senior management team;
to be overall in-charge and responsible for year-end closing.
others
to be responsible in generating and implementing cross-cutting synergies and fields of action for the improvement of internal processes.
to ensure a competitive cost structure and process efficiency within the commercial operations to ensure a vibrant manufacturing location
to be overall an overseer for central functions such as fico (finance/controlling), compliance & legal, company secretarial related matter, hr dept, admin dept, and it dept.

job responsibilities:
1. responsible for voucher entry and accounting work, able to independently handle company accounting;
2. proficient in preparing financial statements such as balance sheets, income statements, cash flow statements, etc;
3. familiar with the daily tax declaration process and specific operations of the company, responsible for annual report review, final settlement and payment, tax inspection, and other work;
