5. complete industrial and commercial tax declaration work, responsible for tax, statistics, industrial and commercial declaration work, coordinate and handle relevant administrative agency matters;

responsibilities:
responsible for assisting superiors in completing various quality control plans to make the quality control system perfect
responsible for organizing, coordinating, and arranging inspection and test work in the production process in accordance with the "product inspection and test control procedures" to ensure the smoothness of the inspection work during the production process, so as to ensure that all delivered products meet the requirements of customers;
responsible for the follow-up and handling of quality abnormalities in the process, participate in the analysis of daily defective products, and propose improvement methods and suggestions according to the "control procedures for non-conforming products";
participate in the improvement of guest feedback information, implement it, and urge subordinates to implement all improvement actions to prevent similar defects from recurring;
investigate and analyze the causes of serious quality problems caused by missed inspections, formulate improvement actions, and implement them;
develop a training plan, organize the training of inspectors, and conduct skill assessments to ensure that the inspectors have the ability to work.
conduct a preliminary assessment of the rationality of the test fixture and process arrangement and put forward reasonable suggestions.
implement the organization's quality policy, objectives, and various rules and regulations, educate and train inspectors to adhere to the principle of "customer first, high quality and efficiency", and strictly implement inspection requirements;
promptly deal with quality problems arising in the production process and report serious quality problems to superiors and related personnel for follow-up, so as to promote total quality management.
responsible for supervising the lower-level management personnel, strictly supervising the inspection personnel to perform product inspection, and reviewing the records of the quality status

